$2000 USD Bounty here!

If you can find a nice solution to our local dev experience, take home a $2000 USD bounty. We have a very strong feeling the culprit is the App Store. The problem is that refactoring it is a challenge since we have 100+ apps, there are tons of circular dependencies and our `main` branch is constantly merged to, making conflicts hard to work around.

Take these PRs as inspiration to ideally not load the entire App Store upon any given page load in our app. If you debug locally and watch what happens in the `.next/server/chunks` folder, you will see it's compiling a ton of code that's not needed.

These PRs have gotten close but refactoring the test suite to continue passing has been quite a blocker.

shared-qmi: fix byteorder for supl server IP

It was noted, that when supl server is set using IP address. Modem
doesn't connect to the SUPL server anymore. When IP address is inverted,
then modem connects to SUPL server successfuly.

IP address is stored as uint32_t. According to Telit's documentation [1]
numeric values are encoded in little-endian format in QMI.

After converting IP address from string to binary using inet_pton
IP address is stored in network byte order (big-endian). Therefore it's
needed another convertion from big-endian to host endianness. Final
conversion from host endianness to endianness needed for QMI will be
done in generated
qmi_message_pds_set_agps_config_input_set_location_server_address.

Vendor's Android GNSS hal uses htonl() to convert from struct in_addr
(already in big-endian) before sending QMI request as well [2].

Tested on Quectel EG25-G and SDM845 (OnePlus 6T).

1. FN980 Family Telit Proprietary QMI Command Reference Guide. 4.1.3.1 Byte Ordering
2. https://github.com/ugly-kid-af/device_xiaomi_violet/blob/snow/gps/gnss/GnssAdapter.cpp#L1110

Signed-off-by: Andrey Skvortsov <andrej.skvortzov@gmail.com>

shared-qmi: always set NMEA types

By default, the Pixel 3a only emits $PQXXX traces, even when all the
desired traces are reported as enabled. A request to set the NMEA types
must still be sent to enable the GGA/GSA/GSV traces. Remove the
optimization that prevents the request from happening automatically.

Signed-off-by: Richard Acayan <mailingradian@gmail.com>

shared-qmi: Lock and unlock GPS engine when starting and stopping

Newer modem firmware requires the use of the GPS engine lock, which
controls what the GPS engine can do. Set the GPS engine lock when
appropriate to handle this newer firmware.

Signed-off-by: Richard Acayan <mailingradian@gmail.com>

shared-qmi: Register NMEA types indication callbacks earlier

It might be too late to register the indication callbacks after the
response is received. Register the callbacks when the request is made so
an requested indication will always be handled.

Signed-off-by: Richard Acayan <mailingradian@gmail.com>

shared-qmi: fix setting URL to supl server

Function mm_parse_suple_address returns TRUE on valid input data
regardless of its type (URL or IP). As a result
qmi_message_loc_set_server_input_set_ipv4 was always called on valid
data. If URL was provided, then 0.0.0.0 ip address was sent to the
modem instead of provided URL.

issue.title: Run a server in bare streams console mode?  ( Trying to setup an Abiotic Factor Server )
issue.body:
I have a VM on a server that I'm trying to run an Abiotic Factor server on.  There isn't even really a GPU.

I've mostly followed directions from these links for dependencies:
https://github.com/DFJacob/AbioticFactorDedicatedServer/issues/3
https://github.com/DFJacob/AbioticFactorDedicatedServer/wiki/Guide-%E2%80%90-Quickstart
Then setup xrdp (and a DE) and umu-run

I suspect the winetricks aren't required but they're part of my present wine environment from earlier tests / attempts.

Currently I installed Linux Steam to the VM and have signed in, but that step might not be necessary; however it seemed to be required to get the game server to proceed past initial startup.

### There's an obvious wine / umu issue.

Umu: The game still runs inside of a new cmd console window, rather than as "bare streams" (stdin/stdout/stderr) ( https://gitlab.winehq.org/wine/wine/-/wikis/Wine-User's-Guide#text-mode-programs-cui-console-user-interface ) on the invoking console.  It'd be MUCH more useful but I don't see any documentation about how to force the program to run like a Linux shell program.


```
#!/bin/sh

/usr/games/steamcmd +@sSteamCmdForcePlatformType windows +force_install_dir steam +login anonymous +app_update 2857200 validate +quit

#GAME="${1:-steam/AbioticFactor/Binaries/Win64/AbioticFactorServer-Win64-Shipping.exe}"
GAME="${1:-steam/AbioticFactorServer.exe}"
shift || true
ls -l "${GAME}"
cd "${GAME%/*}"
GAME="${GAME##*/}"

export WINEPREFIX="${HOME}/wine"
#export GAMEID=:umu-dauntless
export GAMEID=0
#export STORE=egs
export PROTONPATH="GE-Proton"
export STEAM_COMPAT_LIBRARY_PATHS="steam"

umu-run winetricks corefonts
umu-run winetricks vcrun2012
umu-run winetricks vcrun2013
umu-run winetricks vcrun2022

umu-run "${GAME}" \
        -log \
        -useperfthreads \
        -MaxServerPlayers=6 \
        -Port=7777 -QueryPort=27015 -tcp \
        -ServerPassword=Example -AdminPassword=Example -SteamServerName=umutest
```

### Bonus Question / Problem

The game complains about 'Steam Dedicated Server API failed to initialize.'

I am loath to use Discord as a support channel, as this does not generate open Internet index-able documentation that others may build off of for their own knowledge base and problem resolution.

Additionally this might be the point where someone who knows more about umu-launcher / umu-run might just reply.  'That means it only works when launched from steam.'  Which would be a complete pain were that the case.  I'm hoping to get it working and par back to just an easy to CLI manage setup.

issue.title: fix: handle locals() calls in wrapped modules by static analysis
issue.body:
## Summary

This PR fixes bundling of modules that use `locals()` to dynamically access imported symbols, a pattern used by libraries like httpx to set `__module__` attributes.

## Changes

- **Static analysis for `locals()` calls**: When a module-level `locals()` call is detected, it's replaced with a statically determined dictionary containing all module-level symbols
- **`__all__` reference detection**: Added detection for when `__all__` variable is referenced elsewhere in the module (e.g., in loops), ensuring it's preserved when needed
- **AST builder enhancement**: Added `dict()` and `dict_item()` helper functions to the ast_builder for cleaner dictionary construction
- **Test fixture**: Added test case based on httpx's pattern of using `locals()` to access imported symbols

## Problem & Solution

The issue occurred when bundling modules that use this pattern:
```python
from ._internal import MyClass, my_func
__all__ = ["MyClass", "my_func"]
__locals = locals()  # Capture module-level locals
for __name in __all__:
    setattr(__locals[__name], "__module__", "mypkg")
```

In the bundled wrapper function, `locals()` returns function-local variables, not the imported symbols which are now global. The solution uses static analysis to determine what `locals()` would return at module level and replaces it with a dictionary literal containing the correct symbols.

## Test Results

- ✅ All existing tests pass
- ✅ New test fixture for the httpx pattern works correctly
- ✅ Clippy validation passes (only unused `dict_item` warning, kept for future use)

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)

- New Features
  - Wrapper modules now initialize once, are ordered by dependencies, and wire imports immediately during wrapper init.

- Bug Fixes
  - locals()/globals() introspection now reliably reference the module namespace; __all__ is propagated only when actually referenced.

pull_request.title: feat(map): persist and restore selected map type
pull_request.body:
This introduces functionality to save and automatically restore the user's selected map type (both standard Google Maps types and custom tile provider URLs) across app sessions.

The selected map type is now stored in SharedPreferences. When the MapViewModel is initialized, it attempts to load the previously selected map type.

Specific changes include:
- Added new preference keys `PREF_SELECTED_GOOGLE_MAP_TYPE` and `PREF_SELECTED_CUSTOM_TILE_URL`.
- Implemented `loadPersistedMapType()` to retrieve and apply the saved map type on startup. This function includes logic to validate saved custom URLs and fallback to defaults if a saved type is no longer valid.
- Modified `removeCustomTileProviderConfig` to also clear the custom URL from preferences if it was the selected one.
- Updated `selectCustomTileProvider` to save the selected custom URL to preferences and clear any selected Google Map type.
- Updated `setSelectedGoogleMapType` to save the selected Google Map type to preferences and clear any selected custom URL.
- Ensured that when a custom tile provider is selected, or an invalid one is attempted, the corresponding preference is updated or cleared.
- When loading, if a saved custom URL is no longer in the list of available custom tile providers or is invalid, it is cleared from preferences, and the map defaults to the standard Google Map type.
- Added error handling for loading persisted Google Map types in case the stored name is invalid.
